  "prompt": "What does Brain engineers do?",
  "response": "Brain engineers, also known as neural engineers or neurotechnologists, work at the intersection of neuroscience, engineering, and computer science to develop technologies and solutions related to the brain. Their work typically involves:\n\n1. Brain-Computer Interfaces (BCIs)\n- Developing systems that allow direct communication between the brain and external devices\n- Creating technologies for people with disabilities to control prosthetics or computers\n\n2. Neural Imaging and Mapping\n- Designing advanced neuroimaging techniques\n- Creating tools to understand brain structure and function\n- Developing technologies to map neural networks\n\n3. Neuroprosthetics\n- Designing artificial neural systems and neural implants\n- Creating devices to restore sensory or motor functions\n- Developing advanced prosthetic limbs with neural control\n\n4. Neurotechnology Research\n- Studying brain signals and neural mechanisms\n- Developing computational models of brain function\n- Exploring machine learning and AI applications in neuroscience\n\n5. Medical Applications\n- Creating treatments for neurological disorders\n- Developing rehabilitation technologies\n- Designing diagnostic tools for brain-related conditions\n\n6. Neuroengineering\n- Applying engineering principles to understand and manipulate neural systems\n- Developing strategies for neural repair and regeneration\n\nTheir work spans academic research, medical technology, and innovative product development.",
